Deductive databases can be used for building intelligent information systems . Logic programming provides a powerful declarative language for accessing and maintaining knowledge in databases . In addition , techniques from automated deduction and deductive databases are useful for achieving efficient retrieval and reasoning in large knowledge bases . Recent results in logic programming , constraint logic programming , program transformation and optimization , and non-monotonic reasoning are useful for extending the expressive power and the computational efficiency of deductive database systems . With the goal of creating opportunities for active discussions on new research directions and the exchange of latest results in the above areas , we are organizing a one day workshop , with presentations of half an hour . This will be the sixth in a series of DDLP workshops that have been held in conjunction with ICLP conferences since 1993 .
